369
00:16:39,208 --> 00:16:41,208
I know I've heard about
something like that before.

370
00:16:41,416 --> 00:16:44,000
Don't you remember,
the banana whatever?

371
00:16:44,208 --> 00:16:45,833
The Panama Canal?

372
00:16:46,041 --> 00:16:48,500
The one that was almost
fully dried up after some

373
00:16:48,708 --> 00:16:51,708
3,700 odd years of neglect?

374
00:16:51,916 --> 00:16:52,833
Interesting.

375
00:16:53,041 --> 00:16:54,583
I can't help but wonder, it's

376
00:16:54,791 --> 00:16:56,583
connecting two bodies of water

377
00:16:56,791 --> 00:16:58,375
at the same elevation.

378
00:16:58,375 --> 00:17:00,833
So the odds of it working are
totes better than in Panama.

379
00:17:01,041 --> 00:17:01,875
Ha.

380
00:17:02,083 --> 00:17:03,125
If taking that shortcut

381
00:17:03,333 --> 00:17:04,750
will save us an entire year,

382
00:17:04,958 --> 00:17:06,875
then as far as I'm concerned,
we have to try it.

383
00:17:07,083 --> 00:17:07,833
Typical.

384
00:17:08,041 --> 00:17:08,833
Kohaku's rushing

385
00:17:09,041 --> 00:17:10,083
straight into danger.

386
00:17:10,291 --> 00:17:11,166
I can still remember

387
00:17:11,375 --> 00:17:12,208
the sting of having to give

388
00:17:12,416 --> 00:17:14,291
